The '''[[alcohol laws|alcohol licensing laws]] of [[Ireland]]''' regulate the sale and consumption of [[alcohol]]. The legislation controlling licensing regulations is the Intoxicating Liquor Act 2008, Intoxicating Liquor Act 2003, Intoxicating Liquor Act 2000, the [[Licensing Act 1872]] and the Criminal Justice (Public Order) Act 1994.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.citizensinformation.ie/en/justice/criminal_law/criminal_offences/alcohol_and_the_law.html|title=Alcohol and the law|accessdate=11 August 2013}}</ref> The [[International Agency for Research on Cancer]], part of the [[World Health Organization]], has classified alcohol as a class one carcinogenic.<ref>(IRAC, agents classified by the IRAC monographs, vol 1-20). </ref>
