{{Infobox government agency |agency_name = Electoral Commission of South Africa |type = Commission |nativename = |nativename_a = |nativename_r = |logo = IEC SA logo.svg |logo_width = 150px |logo_caption = |seal = |seal_width = |seal_caption = |picture = |picture_width = |picture_caption = |formed = {{Start date|1996|10|17|df=y}} |preceding1 = |preceding2 = <!-- (etc.) --> |dissolved = |superseding = |jurisdiction = [[Government of South Africa]] |headquarters = Election House, [[Centurion, Gauteng|Centurion]] |coordinates = |employees = |budget = |minister1_name = |minister1_pfo = |minister2_name = |minister2_pfo = <!-- (etc.) --> |deputyminister1_name = |deputyminister1_pfo = |deputyminister2_name = |deputyminister2_pfo = <!-- (etc.) --> |chief1_name = Vuma Mashinini |chief1_position = Chairperson |chief2_name = Mosotho Moepya |chief2_position = acting Chief Electoral Officer <!-- (etc.) --> |agency_type = |parent_department = |parent_agency = |child1_agency = |child2_agency = <!-- (etc.) --> |keydocument1 = [[Constitution of South Africa]], s.&nbsp;190 |keydocument2 = Electoral Commission Act, 1996 |keydocument3 = Electoral Act, 1998 <!-- (etc.) --> |website = {{URL|http://www.elections.org.za}} |footnotes = |map = |map_width = |map_caption = }} The '''Electoral Commission of South Africa''' (often referred to as the '''Independent Electoral Commission''' or '''IEC''') is [[South Africa]]'s [[election management body]], an independent organisation established under [[Chapter nine institutions|chapter nine]] of the [[Constitution of South Africa|Constitution]]. It conducts elections to the [[National Assembly (South Africa)|National Assembly]], [[provincial legislature (South Africa)|provincial legislatures]] and [[municipalities of South Africa|municipal councils]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nationalgovernment.co.za/units/view/55/electoral-commission-iec-of-south-africa|title=Electoral Commission (IEC) of South Africa - Overview|website=nationalgovernment.co.za|language=en|access-date=2018-07-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.sahistory.org.za/article/independent-electoral-commission-iec-1996|title=Independent Electoral Commission (IEC) 1996|last=Abongile|date=2014-04-24|work=South African History Online|access-date=2018-07-19|language=en}}</ref>
A temporary Electoral Commission was created in 1993 to manage the [[South African general election, 1994|first non-racial election]] of the national and provincial legislatures, which was held on 26–29 April 1994.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.saflii.org/za/legis/num_act/ieca1993321/|title=Independent Electoral Commission Act, 1993 [No. 150 of 1993] - G 15183|website=www.saflii.org|access-date=2018-07-19}}</ref> The permanent Electoral Commission was established on 17 October 1996,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.elections.org.za/content/Documents/Laws-and-regulations/Electoral-Commission/Electoral-Commission-Act-51-of-1996-including-Regulations/|title=Electoral Commission Act-51 of 1996, including Regulations|last=|first=|date=|website=www.elections.org.za|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=19 July 2018}}</ref> and has since managed general (national and provincial) elections in [[South African general election, 1999|1999]], [[South African general election, 2004|2004]], [[South African general election, 2009|2009]] and [[South African general election, 2014|2014]], and local (municipal) elections in [[South African municipal election, 2000|2000]], [[South African municipal election, 2006|2006]], [[South African municipal election, 2011|2011]] and [[South African municipal election, 2016|2016]].
