The '''Joint Committee on Consolidation, &c., Bills''' is a joint [[Select Committee (Westminster System)|select committee]] of the [[British House of Commons|House of Commons]] and [[British House of Lords|House of Lords]] in the [[Parliament of the United Kingdom]]. The Committee was first established in 1894 with a remit to consider [[consolidation bill]]s.<ref>[http://www.parliament.uk/parliamentary_committees/joint_committee_on_consolidation___c___bills.cfm Joint Committee on Consolidation, &c., Bills] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071102160140/http://www.parliament.uk/parliamentary_committees/joint_committee_on_consolidation___c___bills.cfm |date=2007-11-02 }}</ref> The Committee, which also considers [[Statute Law Revision Bills]] and bills prepared by the [[Law Commission (England and Wales)|Law Commission]] or [[Scottish Law Commission]] to repeal outdated laws,<ref>See [[Statute Law (Repeals) Act]]</ref> is made up of 12 of each House. Bills considered by the Committee originate in the Lords and are referred to it after [[Reading (legislature)|second reading]]. After the Committee reports, the remaining stages in both Houses proceed formally (i.e., without debate).<ref>[http://www.parliament.uk/documents/commons-information-office/l01.pdf Factsheet: Parliamentary Stages of a Government Bill], p. 8.</ref>
==Membership==
As of 16 May 2012, the members of the committee are as follows: * '''Chair:''' [[Robert Carswell, Baron Carswell|Lord Carswell]] (Crossbench) * [[Alan Campbell, Baron Campbell of Alloway|Lord Campbell of Alloway]] (Conservative) * [[Tony Christopher, Baron Christopher|Lord Christopher]] (Labour) * [[Alexander Scrymgeour, 12th Earl of Dundee|Earl of Dundee]] (Conservative) * [[Robin Eames, Baron Eames|Lord Eames]] (Crossbench) * [[Greville Janner, Baron Janner of Braunstone|Lord Janner of Braunstone]] (Labour) * [[Ann Mallalieu, Baroness Mallalieu|Baroness Mallalieu]] (Labour) * [[Robert Methuen, 7th Baron Methuen|Lord Methuen]] (Liberal Democrat) * [[Tim Razzall, Baron Razzall|Lord Razzall]] (Liberal Democrat) * [[Roger Swinfen Eady, 3rd Baron Swinfen|Lord Swinfen]] (Conservative) * [[Francis Tombs, Baron Tombs|Lord Tombs]] (Crossbench) * [[Robert Buckland]] (Conservative) * [[Martin Caton]] (Labour) * [[Jenny Chapman]] (Labour) * [[Damian Collins]] (Conservative) * [[Jim Dobbin]] (Labour Co-op) * [[Stephen Dorrell]] (Conservative) * [[Charlie Elphicke]] (Conservative) * [[Paul Farrelly]] (Labour) * [[Yvonne Fovargue]] (Labour) * [[Jesse Norman]] (Conservative) * [[Sir Robert Smith, 3rd Baronet|Sir Robert Smith]] (Liberal Democrat) * [[Justin Tomlinson]] (Conservative)
